<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-86-1530 </DOCNO><TEXT>Resonances of light nuclei are related to special simple nuclear states.Experimental investigations of alpha and /sup 16/O resonance scatteringon /sup 24/Mg nuclei had double aims: to get direct information aboutthe structure of the compound nuclei formed in the reaction, and to testthe data evaluation and theoretical interpretation methods and models,which relate the measured correlations, angular and energy distributionsto the existence of resonances and special nuclear states. The measureddata were analyzed by an R matrix method, extended to nuclei with spin,and the background was described by DWBA. The applied method combinesdirect and resonance contributions to the scattering amplitudes. (D.G.).</TEXT></DOC>